text: Land van Cuijk is a municipality in the province of North Brabant, the Netherlands. As of 2022, about 90,000 people are living there. It was established by a merger of Boxmeer, Cuijk, Grave, Mill en Sint Hubert, and Sint Anthonis on 1 January 2022. == Other websites == * Official website Category:2022 establishments in the Netherlands
